      "description": "<p>You are part of the Examination Board's IT division, since the Board is in an automation spree. This time an app is being developed to announce their results. Results are stored in DB and successful students roll numbers are assumed to be fetched and stored in an array, to reduce latency &amp; avoid multiple visits to DB. Students should be able to feed their roll nos and search if their number is found in the List of successful candidates<br></p><p><br><strong>You are assigned the task of creating search module:</strong><br>1. an Array of rollNumbers is given&nbsp;[which is assumed to be populated]<br>3. Given a rollNumber, search from the array and display \"Pass\" if found and display \"Failed\" if not found<br>\n\n</p><p><strong>You are asked to use Binary Search</strong><br>\n</p>",
